	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[4.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>To all of you wizards out there. I have a level 16 High elf wizard, who is somewhat twinked at 174 int and around 100 bonus mana. I also have a level 20 warrior, and an IRL friend with a 54 mage who I will be using as a comparison (I have watched him play many many times).<br><br>I think that Wizards are very underpowered. My main comparison is the abilities of the Mage versus those of the Wizard. Verant says that Wizards are the 'masters of damage'. Well, first of all, Mages often nuke within 5% of the power of Wizards at any time, and for comparable mana efficiency. They also have small mana regen self-buffs to make up for this. At the most, Ice Comet outdamages the 49 Mage nuke by a factor of about 300. This is the only big advantage we have over them. 1 spell. 'What about Sunstrike' you say? Well, think about this. It has a long casting time, and can be resisted on the boss mobs that you will most definitly be fighting at this level pretty often.<br><br>Another thing. The Lure spells and the Wizard's so-called 'less resisted' bonus; on raids, mage nukes still get through for good damage. Now, factor in their pet attacking (probably enchanted with Burnout III) and their whole party and the pet enchanted with a DS. Within around 3 seconds, the mob has taken enough damage from the DS and the pet's melee that any damage difference between the current Mage and Wizard nuke is made up quickly. And port spells? Yes, that is an advantage, but Druids can do it too. Druids can also nuke for 1000+ as we can, heal, buff, DoT, and use pets. What do we have over them? 50 damage and VISION SPELLS? Yeah, whatever.<br><br>I am annoyed that Wizards seem to be forgotten by Verant. Even if you don't compare them to other casters, Melees will soon outdamage us (if they haven't already). A high 50s Monk, complete with nice weapons and haste buffs and armor, could probably get in around 300-400 damage at a minimum per spell we get off. Except we're spending mana and they're not. What's up with that? Rogues can backstab for 400+ as well. With better and better weapons coming out, but no spell damage enhancing items or a higher int cap being implemented, casters (especially wizards) are become outclassed.<br><br>Although I have not been playing EverQuest myself for long, I have been observing other people play (I also have a friend with 2 level 60 chars; a 60 mage and a 60 warrior). So I know what I'm talking about. If any of you share my views on this, please respond to the post. If you disagree with any of these points, please provide an arguement with supporting details and points, then I will listen.<br><br>Arendor 16th Wizard<br>Duergar 20th Warrior<br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
