	   <a name=100576452849199></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100576452849199><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=11&mid=100576452849199>RE: why are we hated</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=11&mid=100576452849199#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=44109><span id= >Zigon</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>9 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Nov 14th 2:02 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Through most of your Wizard's life you will find it hard to find groups.&nbsp;&nbsp;The main reason is that it takes a long time to learn how to play a wizard correctly.<br><br>Wizards can outdamage most tanks.  The exception to this is when a tank gets heals and the fight is long.  (When are we going to get a complete mana recharge spell so our mana is refilled just like a tanks health)<br><br>The main trick to playing a wizard is to not pull agro unless you want to be smacked down.  Belive me, there are times when you want yourself to die instead of a cleric.<br>  <br>The best method is to let the tank hit the mob until it is about 20% hurt.  Agro has been built up on the tank.  Then you let lose with a nuke.  Don't chain nuke.  See if the mob comes at you.  It it does you either a) nuked too soon b) nuked too hard c) nuked with a stun (stuns add extra agro).<br><br>If you didn't pull agro with the nuke, then sit to med.  If mob comes at you then you sat too soon.  If the mob doesn't come at you then you are safe to med.  Once the mob is mostly dead (about a quarter of its life left) let it have it with 1 or 2 more nukes.<br><br>This is different if you have multiple adds.  Your way of controlling the crowd is if you can blast one mob out of existance without you dieing or you can attempt the root and hold them away technique.  Either one runs its own risks because if you root a mob without a tank engaging it for agro it will come at you first.  If you chain nuke a mob dead you will get the agro and possibly the social agro of the other mob.  As you may have noticed you do not have alot of AC or alot of HP.<br><br>The hardest levels are the teens to the mid 30s.  At the majority of these levels you will need to be in groups. But you also face the problem of Mages also being able to match you nuke for nuke (in some cases able to out nuke you) and if you add their pets, outright blow your damage output away.<br><br>At the higher levels (29+) you can learn to kite.  You can not quad kite decently until level 34 when you get circle of force.  Do not attempt to quad kite with al'kabor line of spells.  You will go OOM before you finish it of.<br><br>At even higher levels 50+ you will notice that you can land nukes on mobs where mages can't.  Once you get Draughts and lures that is even more prevalent.  The exception is do not try to nuke jade reavers.  They will resists just about every lure you throw at them.  (the fair thing Verant should do is make mobs untouchable by anything short of spell nukes - but still hold agro on anyone swinging at them)<br><br>I am a level 54 wizard and I have surprised people in my guild with the amount of damage I can put out is a short amount of time.  The drawback is I then have to meditate to get my mana back.  Until I do I am just a short live meat shield. <br><br>I still have trouble finding dungeon crawling groups so I now look for kiting groups.  Yes, you can quad kite with other area nukers.  You can also solo kite with others on solo mobs.  Just continually use your Staff of Temperate flux to grab and hold agro while they nuke/hit/DoT away.  Just make sure you have SoW going.  Jboots on some of these mobs isn't fast enough.<br><br>The trinity is still the majority of the core pieces of a group (warrior/cleric/enchanter).  But even they sometimes go for a long time LFG.<br><br>I hope this helps some.  I like playing my wizard.  I don't like solo kiting for exp but that seems to be about the only way I can get exp.  I do like group kiting.  Gives me someone to talk to during mana recharge times.  (BTW - I am great at gems = too much solo kiting)<br><br>Zigon Zagoff<br>54 channeler<br>Vazaelle<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
