	   <tr><td colspan=2>Ok, not every spell is buyable. Alot can only be researched and some you can do both. you might get lucky and see a researched spell at a merchant but it's only because a wiz made and sold it for a few plat instead of selling to another wiz. The ones you can research will save you money instead of buying them.<br><br>The monther of all research is Ice Comet (lvl 49). you might be able to buy it for a few hundred plat off another wiz (500pp on innoruuk about 2 weeks ago in EC) or take the time to research it. I researched Ice Comet with a 131 skill and a 150 wisdom on the first try (shoot for atleast a 160 skill, I think I was lucky). The runes drop off high level mobs in Kunark and velious (also naggy and vox) OR the old way was to do the Staff of the Wheel quest, turn the staff in for the runes. (do the quest anyway, great staff and considered the first test of a wizard by many).<br><br>wait till lvl 20 to start research. your base skill will be higher than starting at 16. Besides, the level 16 spells are a waste of mana and you won't be missing anything by waiting. Once at 20 put 1 point into research at the quild and start doing the "concordance of research quests". Do the low level research quests to get your skill up. SAVE THE PRACTICE POINTS until you really need them, trust me you will know when.<br><br>Good rune drop zones? Oasis, Loio and Mistmore. Tell your group when you join (or start) that you get all the runes, the pages, tombs and words will go to those classes that need them. This way you will save money from having to by real runes at the vendors.<br><br>for bank storage, take the boat to Ice clad (from nro) and go to the gnome outpost (little danger in the trip, did it at 4lvl). There is a guy that sells a gnome toolbox that has 10 slots for just over 1plat and hold giant sized stuff (hes in an igloo). Buy all you can fit/carry and gate home then, put these in your bank slots. they are much cheaper than the 10 slot backbacks and are perfect for bank storage. Now you have room to store runes, and store you will. save every rune you can, even if it not needed for 20 levels! trust me, thay can be hard to come by when you need one.<br><br>hope it helps.&nbsp;&nbsp;=)<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
