	   <tr><td colspan=2>I'm a lvl 48 Wizard now.&nbsp;&nbsp;I played in Oasis until about lvl 18.  Played in Orc groups and somtimes soloed a croc or 2.  Then on to East Karana where I fought Dark Stalkers and Gorge Hounds, sometimes solo, sometimes with a partner.  When I made 20 I went to SK to start killin Aviaks.  Did that until about 23 then I started lookin for Gnoll Spire groups in SK.  Was able to get some great xp at this lvl when grouping at spires.  Got in a Paw dungeon group at 24 a few times and flew thru lvl 24.  I stayed at Spires until about 35, making trips back and forth from LOIO for some variety.  After you get Bonds of Force at lvl 29, you can start soloing much easier.  Try your hardest to get some high lvl chars to help you get Jboots.  Jboots+BoF=easy soloin :)  I went to Iceclad and fought cougars thru Hell lvl.  Picked up a couple of earrings too.  Then I went to the East Wastes and fought Ulthorks and Walruses.  There is great exp here!  You won't believe how much blue you get when you kill an Ulthork.  Plus theres lots of good loot.  I foguth here until recently.  Also spent time in Great Divide killin Giants, and in Rathe makin money off Hill Giants.  At 48 I'm wasting time twinkin all my alts LOL!  Man have I spent a lot of dough on them :(  Hmm  any suggestions on where to go at 48?<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
