	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Oct 29th 2:07 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.17]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Evocation is your skill for your DD spells. But over the course of gaining levels you will be able to max out evocation and channeling pretty quickly. I recommend putting points or practicing your other magic skills such conjuration, abjuration, divination and alteration.&nbsp;&nbsp;Nothing is worse than having a spell you can't cast because you don't have the skill to cast it.  I found this out with my ranger when I ignored conjuration for 21 levels finally get a DoT spell and had to use my whole mana bar just to cast it once. Since then I keep all my magic skills maxed each level.<br><br>Cannis Skywise<br>45th Ranger<br>Dreavien<br>15th Wizard<br>Bertoxxulous<br>&nbsp;<br>Cannis 60th Ranger<br></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
